<%= content_for :title, "Accessibility Statement - MedGemma Health" %>
<%= content_for :meta_description, "MedGemma Health's commitment to digital accessibility ensuring our services are accessible to all users, including those with disabilities." %>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="pt-32 pb-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-purple-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12" data-controller="fade-in">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 rounded-full mb-6">
        <i class="fas fa-universal-access text-purple-600 mr-2"></i>
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-purple-800">Inclusion</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
        Accessibility 
        <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-indigo-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          Statement
        </span>
      </h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Last Updated: May 25, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Accessibility Content -->
<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-purple max-w-none" data-controller="fade-in">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
        <p>
          MedGemma Health is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards to achieve this.
        </p>
        <p>
          We strive to ensure that our website, mobile applications, and digital services comply with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards and Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Measures We Take</h2>
        
        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Technical Accessibility</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-purple-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Accessible navigation that can be operated using keyboard-only controls</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-purple-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Text alternatives for all non-text content</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-purple-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Proper semantic HTML to ensure compatibility with screen readers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-purple-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Sufficient color contrast ratios for text and interactive elements</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-purple-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Resizable text without loss of content or functionality</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Content Design Practices</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-indigo-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Clear and consistent navigation throughout the platform</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-indigo-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Descriptive link text that explains where links lead</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-indigo-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Headings and landmarks to help navigate content</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-indigo-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Form fields with associated labels and accessible error messages</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-indigo-500 mt-1 mr-2"></i>
              <span>Captions and transcripts for multimedia content</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Accessibility Features</h2>
        <p>
          Our platform includes several accessibility features to enhance usability:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Text Adjustment:</strong> Users can adjust text size using browser controls without loss of functionality.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Screen Reader Support:</strong> Our content is structured to work with popular screen readers such as JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, and TalkBack.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> All interactive elements are accessible via keyboard, with visible focus indicators.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Alternative Text:</strong> Images have appropriate alt text descriptions for screen reader users.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Color and Contrast:</strong> Text and interactive elements have sufficient color contrast for users with visual impairments.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Form Accessibility:</strong> All form fields have clear labels and instructions, with error messages that are announced to screen readers.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Continuous Improvement</h2>
        <p>
          We are continuously working to improve the accessibility of our services through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
          <li>User feedback and usability testing</li>
          <li>Accessibility training for our development and content teams</li>
          <li>Staying updated with the latest accessibility standards and best practices</li>
          <li>Engaging with the disability community to better understand their needs</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Despite our best efforts, some content may not yet meet our accessibility goals. We are actively working to address these issues.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Assistive Technologies Supported</h2>
        <p>
          Our platform is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Screen readers (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, TalkBack)</li>
          <li>Speech recognition software</li>
          <li>Screen magnification tools</li>
          <li>Alternative input devices</li>
          <li>Browser accessibility extensions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Feedback and Assistance</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of MedGemma Health. If you encounter accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mt-4">
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> accessibility@medgemmahealth.com</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Phone:</strong> (800) 555-0124</p>
          <p>
            <strong>Postal Address:</strong><br>
            MedGemma Health<br>
            Attn: Accessibility Team<br>
            123 Health Avenue<br>
            San Francisco, CA 94107
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days, and to propose a solution within 10 business days.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Legal Compliance</h2>
        <p>
          MedGemma Health is committed to compliance with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</li>
          <li>Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</li>
          <li>Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</li>
          <li>Applicable state and international accessibility laws and regulations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This accessibility statement was prepared on May 25, 2025 and will be regularly reviewed and updated.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA Section -->
<section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center" data-controller="fade-in">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Need Assistance?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        We're here to help you navigate our platform and resolve any accessibility issues you might encounter.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-purple-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-purple-700 transition-colors">
          <i class="fas fa-envelope mr-2"></i>
          Contact Support
        </a>
        <a href="/help-center" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-white border border-gray-300 text-gray-700 font-medium rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle mr-2"></i>
          Visit Help Center
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
